The Department of Health in Limpopo says 104 travellers have tested positive for coronavirus at the Beitbridge Border post in past four days. This comes as scores of Zimbabweans make their way back to South Africa following the festive season holiday period. In the video below, Limpopo Health MEC Dr Phophi Ramathuba gave an update of COVID-19 in the province:  In a statement, Limpopo Health MEC Dr Phophi Ramathuba calls on travellers who have been at the port of entry in the past four days to self isolate as soon as they reach their homes. She says with the large numbers of travellers that the border post has seen in the said four days, people that were there have been exposed to a potential super spreader locations. Latest on SA Stats  SOURCE: Department of Health  & ﻿National Institute of Communicable Diseases  CASES GAUTENG WESTERN CAPE KWAZULU-NATAL EASTERN CAPE FREE STATE LIMPOPO NORTH WEST MPUMALANGA NORTHERN CAPE 236 ﻿177 177 ﻿314 32 ﻿493 41 ﻿927 UNALLOCATED 0 8 ﻿362 647 671 DEATHS 2 ﻿238 7 ﻿822 5 ﻿998 5 ﻿002 648 421 86163 315 ﻿738 44 ﻿255 26 ﻿701 231 ﻿060  Free State  North West  Gauteng  Mpumalanga  Northern Cape Eastern Cape  Limpopo  KwaZulu-Natal Western Cape 64 925 AS AT 7 JANUARY 2021 1 170 590 31 809 6 967 478 938 216 20 999 441 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));